00:22:14.760 --> 00:22:15.960
After this morning. I--

472
00:22:16.440 --> 00:22:18.520
I wasn't sure
you'd ever want to see me again.

473
00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:22.040
Come in.

474
00:22:25.440 --> 00:22:27.720
Why did you really come back. Terry?

475
00:22:28.360 --> 00:22:29.720
I wanted to see you.

476
00:22:31.000 --> 00:22:34.520
Tasha.
you said that you would divorce James

477
00:22:34.640 --> 00:22:36.520
after he got the Queens Child Project.

478
00:22:37.480 --> 00:22:38.560
Did you mean it?

479
00:22:40.360 --> 00:22:42.640
Yes. I meant it.

480
00:22:44.760 --> 00:22:47.480
-I need to move on.
-Then you should file now.

481
00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:50.120
There's a RICO mounting against James.

482
00:22:50.480 --> 00:22:52.200
Indictments are coming down
in the next few days.

483
00:22:52.560 --> 00:22:53.840
[Tasha] How do you know that?

484
00:22:54.600 --> 00:22:55.880
<i></i>

485
00:22:56.520 --> 00:22:59.400
If you initiate the divorce.
the feds will offer you immunity

486
00:22:59.520 --> 00:23:00.560
to testify against him.

487
00:23:00.920 --> 00:23:03.640
You need to stay out of prison. Tasha.
For your kids.

488
00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:06.760
For me.

489
00:23:11.680 --> 00:23:14.880
Testify about what? He didn't do anything.

490
00:23:15.360 --> 00:23:18.720
Tasha. I know you're innocent morally.
but not technically.

491
00:23:20.120 --> 00:23:22.720
Of everyone implicated.
you have the most to lose.

492
00:23:22.960 --> 00:23:25.680
If you take a deal.
you can walk away from everything. hmm?

493
00:23:26.480 --> 00:23:29.160
Start over... with me.

494
00:23:30.600 --> 00:23:32.240
Live the life we both deserve.

495
00:23:37.400 --> 00:23:39.160
-[Cooper] Lakeisha Grant!
-[car door closes]

496
00:23:41.040 --> 00:23:42.280
You in the wrong neighborhood.

497
00:23:42.440 --> 00:23:44.280
Ooh. actually.
I'm exactly where I need to be.

498
00:23:44.440 --> 00:23:47.920
AUSA Cooper Saxe. I need to talk to you
about Tasha St. Patrick.

499
00:23:48.120 --> 00:23:51.520
-She's an investor in your salon.
-I don't fuck with Tasha.

500
00:23:51.680 --> 00:23:53.400
Mm. what about your. uh...

501
00:23:54.320 --> 00:23:55.840
bae. Tommy Egan?

502
00:23:56.560 --> 00:23:59.680
-I'm not fucking with Tommy. either.
-Hmm. Connie Teresi says different.

503
00:23:59.800 --> 00:24:01.880
She and her husband. Tony. had dinner
with the two of you the other night?

504
00:24:02.400 --> 00:24:05.280
-So what?
-Tommy's in huge trouble. and so are you.

505
00:24:06.520 --> 00:24:07.440
We have reason to believe

506
00:24:07.600 --> 00:24:09.600
you're laundering his drug money
through your shop.

507
00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:13.120
[sighs]

508
00:24:13.440 --> 00:24:14.960
I'll give you a walk on any charges

509
00:24:15.120 --> 00:24:18.040
if you can get Tommy to flip
on James St. Patrick.

510
00:24:19.280 --> 00:24:22.080
Tommy ain't no snitch. And neither am I.

511
00:24:22.840 --> 00:24:27.840
Really? Even if Tommy knew his buddy James
was involved in his father's death?

512
00:24:28.200 --> 00:24:30.000
<i></i>

513
00:24:30.440 --> 00:24:31.840
You're wasting your time.

514
00:24:33.320 --> 00:24:34.240
[sighs]

515
00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:43.200
-Going to the city.
-[car door closes]

516
00:24:43.360 --> 00:24:44.280
[cab driver] Yes. ma'am.

517
00:24:48.160 --> 00:24:49.080
[Joe] James!

518
00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:53.840
I got something for you.

519
00:24:56.760 --> 00:24:58.520
You're not gonna buy me dinner first?

520
00:25:01.920 --> 00:25:05.480
It was one time and under duress.
Jesus Christ!

521
00:25:06.120 --> 00:25:09.640
Besides. that award-winning performance
is the reason why I am no longer

522
00:25:09.760 --> 00:25:11.320
a viable witness against you.

523
00:25:12.160 --> 00:25:14.280
-But Angela--
-Is not turning on me. Joe.

524
00:25:14.400 --> 00:25:15.680
She's protecting me. You know what?

525
00:25:15.800 --> 00:25:17.040
-They brought her in for questioning.
-[sighs]

526
00:25:17.160 --> 00:25:18.160
And guess what. Joe? She didn't break.

527
00:25:18.280 --> 00:25:19.600
-You don't get it. James.
-What don't I get?

528
00:25:19.720 --> 00:25:21.640
-Please enlighten me.
-Well. I'll tell you.

529
00:25:21.920 --> 00:25:24.480
My guy. Charlie. saw FBI windbreakers

530
00:25:24.600 --> 00:25:27.720
coming for re-questioning
on the Lobos transport.

531
00:25:28.440 --> 00:25:32.760
They're trying to link you. Tommy.
and Angela to Lobos and Sandoval.

532
00:25:32.920 --> 00:25:34.160
Well. that's funny. Joe. You know why?

533
00:25:34.280 --> 00:25:36.040
Because you and I sat
in an office and you were colluding

534
00:25:36.160 --> 00:25:38.320
with me and Tommy
to kill Sandoval. not Angela.

535
00:25:38.440 --> 00:25:40.880
Yeah. and my life has turned
into a fucking hell

536
00:25:41.040 --> 00:25:43.360
because I care enough to protect you.

537
00:25:43.560 --> 00:25:45.480
Well. listen to this one.
It doesn't matter

538
00:25:45.600 --> 00:25:47.800
if it's me or Angela that's implicated.

539
00:25:48.160 --> 00:25:51.640
Charlie also saw Saxe
talking to Terry Silver.

540
00:25:52.720 --> 00:25:53.680
Silver's back?

541
00:25:54.560 --> 00:25:57.680
And Silver links all of us
to Sandoval through Angela.

542
00:25:57.880 --> 00:25:58.800
[exhales]

543
00:25:58.920 --> 00:26:00.800
-So if you won't burn her--
-Which I won't.

544
00:26:02.200 --> 00:26:03.880
[Joe] Then we only got one other shot.

545
00:26:05.160 --> 00:26:06.120
Tommy.

546
00:26:06.320 --> 00:26:08.400
-I should fucking kill you.
-Listen to me.

547
00:26:08.560 --> 00:26:09.560
Okay. it works.

548
00:26:09.760 --> 00:26:12.920
You tell the feds
that Teresi called Tommy.

549
00:26:13.040 --> 00:26:15.560
told him Sandoval
was in the Manhattan Correctional Center.

550
00:26:15.760 --> 00:26:18.360
Tommy told dear old dad to merc Sandoval.

551
00:26:18.640 --> 00:26:23.200
That version leaves us all out of it.
me. you. and Angela.

552
00:26:23.440 --> 00:26:26.040
If Terry Silver talks.
he looks like a fucking liar.

553
00:26:26.360 --> 00:26:28.000
And I know what you're going to say.

554
00:26:28.440 --> 00:26:31.040
-You'll never flip on Tommy.
-Which I won't. but you would.

555
00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:34.000
-[Joe sighs]
-How do I know we can trust you?

556
00:26:34.400 --> 00:26:36.000
You would obviously protect
your daughter first.

557
00:26:36.160 --> 00:26:38.080
That's my flesh and blood.

558
00:26:38.400 --> 00:26:40.720
not some fucking delusional fairy tale.

559
00:26:41.960 --> 00:26:44.480
I thought you were smarter than that.
You're getting played.

560
00:26:45.760 --> 00:26:48.800
Come on.
You have to let this Angela thing go.

561
00:26:50.640 --> 00:26:53.480
-[scoffs]
-Bring me anything else you find out.

562
00:26:56.840 --> 00:26:58.200
[car horns honking]

563
00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:00.520
-[lighter flicks]
-[indistinct chatter]

564
00:27:07.880 --> 00:27:09.280
[Angela]
I don't have time for lunch today.

565
00:27:09.400 --> 00:27:11.320
-What's the emergency?
-John Mak came to the salon.

566
00:27:11.720 --> 00:27:14.000
-I'm sorry he bothered you--
-Thank God he did.

567
00:27:14.760 --> 00:27:17.120
You have to take the deal
they're offering. It's your only way out.

568
00:27:17.280 --> 00:27:19.400
-It's not that easy.
-Yes. it is.

569
00:27:20.320 --> 00:27:24.080
You just sign their little piece of paper
and tell them whatever they want.

570
00:27:24.760 --> 00:27:26.360
[in Spanish] I know. You love him.

571
00:27:27.040 --> 00:27:29.880
[in English] But this decision.
isn't just about what you want now.

572
00:27:30.160 --> 00:27:33.040
It's about <i>Papi </i>and Junior and me.

573
00:27:33.720 --> 00:27:35.200
You got to think about your family.

574
00:27:35.840 --> 00:27:39.240
You got to think about your career
that you've worked so hard on.

575
00:27:39.520 --> 00:27:40.880
Are you kidding me? You don't think

576
00:27:41.000 --> 00:27:42.680
I've been thinking about this
from the beginning?

577
00:27:42.880 --> 00:27:43.800
<i></i>

578
00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:46.240
My career is over. Paz.
no matter what I do.

579
00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:48.200
I have to start over entirely.

580
00:27:48.560 --> 00:27:52.000
Then you start over. without Jamie.
without any of that.

581
00:27:52.160 --> 00:27:54.480
-It's not about Jamie.
-It's always about Jamie!

582
00:27:55.000 --> 00:27:56.640
Ever since he came back into your life.

583
00:27:57.280 --> 00:28:00.680
But what is gonna happen
when you lie for him. hmm?

584
00:28:00.960 --> 00:28:03.640
[in Spanish] You can't blow up your life
for him again.

585
00:28:04.160 --> 00:28:06.080
-He's still with his wife.
-No. he's not.

586
00:28:06.480 --> 00:28:08.560
-Plus. she's okay with us now.
-[Paz sighs]

587
00:28:08.680 --> 00:28:09.920
That doesn't matter.

588
00:28:10.720 --> 00:28:14.000
You still think someday
this will all work out.

589
00:28:18.080 --> 00:28:19.800
[in English] You gotta save yourself.

590
00:28:21.400 --> 00:28:23.120
[in Spanish] We'll be here for you.

591
00:28:23.680 --> 00:28:25.000
We'll take care of you.

592
00:28:25.440 --> 00:28:26.760
Even if you have no money.

593
00:28:26.920 --> 00:28:28.920
Even if you have to sleep on my couch.

594
00:28:30.680 --> 00:28:34.320
[in English] At least you'll be safe.
I mean. we'll be together.

595
00:28:35.080 --> 00:28:37.200
I'm trying to get out of it. Paz. okay?

596
00:28:37.960 --> 00:28:40.320
I think I have a way. Can you trust me?

597
00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:48.280
<i></i>

598
00:28:53.840 --> 00:28:55.680
[door locks]

599
00:28:58.320 --> 00:28:59.280
[sighs]

600
00:29:01.360 --> 00:29:04.080
What are you doing here?
You know we can't be seen together.

601
00:29:04.400 --> 00:29:05.520
Angie. calm down.

602
00:29:05.920 --> 00:29:07.560
I took necessary precautions.

603
00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:10.080
-What happened with Proctor?
-It's handled.

604
00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:12.920
-How about Dre?
-It's handled.

605
00:29:13.040 --> 00:29:15.720
Okay. now we just wait.
see how your plan plays out.

606
00:29:16.600 --> 00:29:17.600
[sighs]

607
00:29:21.880 --> 00:29:22.840
So. Angela...

608
00:29:24.080 --> 00:29:25.640
what do we do when this is over?

609
00:29:27.240 --> 00:29:29.000
Jamie. are we still the dream?

610
00:29:29.160 --> 00:29:30.520
<i></i>

611
00:29:32.720 --> 00:29:34.040
As long as you're you and I'm me.

612
00:29:34.160 --> 00:29:35.920
we're always gonna be running
from something.

613
00:29:38.240 --> 00:29:39.720
Is this the ending you wanted?

614
00:29:40.280 --> 00:29:42.760
-What if it's the new beginning?
-We tried that.

615
00:29:42.880 --> 00:29:44.120
[James] Yeah. but not like this.

616
00:29:44.600 --> 00:29:47.560
Now we know the best and worst parts
of each other. It's better than the dream.

617
00:29:48.960 --> 00:29:49.960
It's real.

618
00:29:53.840 --> 00:29:55.840
[sighs]

619
00:29:56.440 --> 00:29:59.120
When you're standing here in front of me.
it feels possible.

620
00:30:01.560 --> 00:30:03.640
But the world outside tells the truth.

621
00:30:04.560 --> 00:30:06.880
[scoffs] It's like what Tasha said before.
right?

622
00:30:07.840 --> 00:30:11.560
-I always save myself. and so do you.
-But now. we're saving each other.

623
00:30:14.960 --> 00:30:16.160
Let's save each other.

624
00:30:26.280 --> 00:30:27.320
You should go.

625
00:30:29.240 --> 00:30:30.360
I'll see you when it's over.

626
00:30:32.080 --> 00:30:33.040
When it's over.

627
00:30:55.320 --> 00:30:56.280
<i></i>

628
00:30:56.440 --> 00:30:59.200
[indistinct chatter]

629
00:31:01.280 --> 00:31:04.480
-[James] This is a great day. right?
-[chuckles] Finally.

630
00:31:04.600 --> 00:31:06.440
Man. finally breaking ground
to honor Raina.

631
00:31:07.400 --> 00:31:09.360
-Very exciting.
-And yet. still not as exciting

632
00:31:09.480 --> 00:31:11.520
as the announcement
for your gubernatorial campaign.

633
00:31:11.960 --> 00:31:13.280
Yeah. about that.

634
00:31:14.240 --> 00:31:15.720
I'm going to postpone my announcement.

635
00:31:16.240 --> 00:31:18.480
I don't want to distract
from Raina's legacy.

636
00:31:19.040 --> 00:31:20.240
No. Rashad. we made a deal.

637
00:31:20.720 --> 00:31:22.400
We said that the coverage
you got for the announcement

638
00:31:22.520 --> 00:31:23.520
would be a boon for our project.

639
00:31:23.800 --> 00:31:25.240
-That was the original agenda.
-But?

640
00:31:25.440 --> 00:31:27.240
There are rumblings
of a federal investigation

641
00:31:27.400 --> 00:31:28.920
into Tommy Egan.

642
00:31:29.760 --> 00:31:31.680
And that could detract from us...

643
00:31:32.520 --> 00:31:34.760
this project. which is very important.

644
00:31:35.480 --> 00:31:37.960
Now listen here. if they ask you to...

645
00:31:39.240 --> 00:31:42.440
-you need to cooperate with them fully.
-Nigga. you from this hood.

646
00:31:43.440 --> 00:31:45.240
You want me to snitch
on my last remaining day one?

647
00:31:45.400 --> 00:31:47.920
If you don't. then both of our careers
are on the line.

648
00:31:48.080 --> 00:31:49.680
And any of this shit blows back onto you.

649
00:31:50.000 --> 00:31:52.320
then I'm gonna have to cooperate with them
if they ask me to.

650
00:31:52.440 --> 00:31:53.720
-I promise you--
-They won't give me a choice.

651
00:31:53.840 --> 00:31:54.840
-James.
-Listen to me. Rashad.

652
00:31:55.040 --> 00:31:57.160
-Listen. I know how this goes.
-Rashad. listen to me!

653
00:31:57.400 --> 00:31:58.360
<i></i>

654
00:31:58.640 --> 00:32:01.480
Now. I just said... it won't get to that.

655
00:32:02.680 --> 00:32:04.040
Everything's under control.

656
00:32:05.760 --> 00:32:07.080
Fucking take a deep breath.

657
00:32:07.400 --> 00:32:09.400
[indistinct chatter]

658
00:32:09.760 --> 00:32:11.840
You have my word.
I want you to get up on that stage.

659
00:32:11.960 --> 00:32:13.680
and give these people your word...

660
00:32:14.880 --> 00:32:16.080
Governor Tate.

661
00:32:17.120 --> 00:32:18.120
[scoffs]

662
00:32:18.400 --> 00:32:19.800
[indistinct chatter]

663
00:32:20.200 --> 00:32:21.400
-All right. [clears throat]
-[man] Here he is.

664
00:32:21.680 --> 00:32:22.920
Councilman Tate from Queens!

665
00:32:23.440 --> 00:32:25.040
[crowd applauding]

666
00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:31.960
Ladies and gentleman.
before I introduce my partner

667
00:32:32.480 --> 00:32:34.600
of the Queens Child Project.
James St. Patrick.

668
00:32:34.760 --> 00:32:37.080
I would like to make
an announcement of my own.

669
00:32:38.800 --> 00:32:40.640
It is with great honor...

670
00:32:41.400 --> 00:32:44.960
that I declare my bid
for governor of New York...

671
00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:47.200
-[crowd exclaims]
-...in this year's upcoming election.

672
00:32:47.600 --> 00:32:48.920
[crowd cheering. applauding]

673
00:32:49.360 --> 00:32:53.800
I'm throwing my hat into the ring
to become the first elected...

674
00:32:54.680 --> 00:32:57.760
Black governor of this great state
of New York!

675
00:32:57.880 --> 00:32:59.000
[crowd cheering. applauding]

676
00:32:59.600 --> 00:33:03.040
Without further ado. my dear partner.
James St. Patrick.

677
00:33:03.440 --> 00:33:05.280
[applauding continues]

678
00:33:05.560 --> 00:33:06.840
Thank you. Rashad.

679
00:33:07.520 --> 00:33:09.760
And there's no doubt that you and I
will be making history together.

680
00:33:10.240 --> 00:33:12.560
It's been a long road
to get to this groundbreaking.

681
00:33:12.800 --> 00:33:14.480
Through my grief. I made mistakes...

682
00:33:15.240 --> 00:33:17.360
perhaps. even made some enemies
along the way.

683
00:33:18.560 --> 00:33:20.080
But I can assure you.
it was all in pursuit

684
00:33:20.200 --> 00:33:23.600
of keeping a part of my baby girl alive.

685
00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:26.280
Our baby girl.

686
00:33:26.640 --> 00:33:29.280
My wife. Tasha.
joins me today in this fight.

687
00:33:29.640 --> 00:33:33.520
[crowd cheering. applauding]

688
00:33:38.040 --> 00:33:40.680
We are both here in the fight
and we finally feel

689
00:33:40.800 --> 00:33:42.120
that we've come to a place
where we can say

690
00:33:42.240 --> 00:33:43.240
that the fight has been won.

691
00:33:43.560 --> 00:33:46.520
This center will serve as a safe haven.

692
00:33:46.800 --> 00:33:48.240
For parents. for children.

693
00:33:48.440 --> 00:33:51.640
It will serve by giving opportunities
to people away from the streets.

694
00:33:52.360 --> 00:33:54.720
Programs that I wish I had
when I was growing up.

695
00:33:55.160 --> 00:33:57.720
When I was the age of these kids.
to make my road a lot easier.

696
00:33:58.160 --> 00:34:02.880
So that no father. no-- no mother.
should ever have to bury their child

697
00:34:03.240 --> 00:34:05.200
due to violence. crime
and drugs ever again.

698
00:34:05.560 --> 00:34:07.680
-<i></i>
-[crowd applauding]

699
00:34:07.920 --> 00:34:09.040
[James] Thank you. guys.

700
00:34:09.920 --> 00:34:12.520
<i></i>

701
00:34:15.200 --> 00:34:18.240
All right. let's start digging.
Children. come on up!

702
00:34:18.560 --> 00:34:20.760
One at a time. come on.
step up. come on. come on.

703
00:34:20.920 --> 00:34:23.240
-Don't bite me. don't bite me.
-[camera shutters clicking]

704
00:34:23.360 --> 00:34:24.960
Get ready. one. two. three.

705
00:34:25.680 --> 00:34:27.040
[crowd cheering]

706
00:34:27.240 --> 00:34:28.680
-What the hell?
-When were you gonna to tell me

707
00:34:28.800 --> 00:34:30.200
that Terry Silver was back in town. Tash?

708
00:34:30.400 --> 00:34:32.160
-Who told you that?
-It don't make no never mind.

709
00:34:32.320 --> 00:34:33.520
Did you know?

710
00:34:33.800 --> 00:34:36.280
[scoffs] I didn't know anything
until this very minute.

711
00:34:37.320 --> 00:34:40.160
You see that. Tasha? I-- I don't know
if I can fucking believe you.

712
00:34:40.560 --> 00:34:41.720
Are you breaking team. huh?

713
00:34:41.840 --> 00:34:43.840
-Is that what you're trying to do here?
-[scoffs] Are you kidding me?

714
00:34:44.000 --> 00:34:46.160
What. I'm-- I'm going to run off
with Terry Silver?

